{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-05335/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-05335"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:53:35"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["extreme close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, pan, tilt"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman speaks, wearing a look of concern."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05335/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-05335","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05335/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-05335"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05335/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05335/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05335/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05335/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05335/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05335/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05335/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05335/canvas/1/cd4b4152-9add-4d89-a7b0-19dea82c340f","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T20:37:20.960Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>When Alma tells Reynolds that Barbara does not deserve to wear the dress, he initially dismisses her comments, telling her not to cry or blubber. Alma, though upset, maintains her composure in the conversation, speaking softly and evenly.&nbsp; He refuses to take her complaints seriously or treat her as an intellectual equal. Perhaps he is projecting his own conflicting emotions onto her, as it's clear that he too is upset to see Barbara wearing his designs. Reynolds immediately assumes she is being overly emotional, hysterical, when she voices the same feelings that he is trying to disregard within himself.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05335/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:529.4503205128212,97.07211538461533,1129.4150641025637,865.8173076923076"}}}]}]}]}